The paper discusses recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on satisfying the needs of multiple stakeholders suggests a potential connection to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories, as these fields often involve balancing the interests of multiple parties. Finally, the mention of practical applications and potential solutions suggests a connection to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which focuses on designing systems that are usable and effective for end users.
